##The Italian apartheid diary | a month later, I met my first Italian

Micro Signal Directorbai

Function description, all my feelings are illuminated by the moonlight.

| | Guo Ronghua

Ronghua lives in Florence, Italy.

Now she is sequestered in her Florentine home by Italy's policy of locking up the country.

The writer is a fiery young woman.

I sit in the living room with my white sheets and check my phone every few seconds. As the hands of the clock ticked around, my heart beat harder in my chest.

The French windows in the kitchen were wide open, and a breeze was probably blowing from the yard, and I could only see the fresh air through the waving of the tablecloth.

I almost bounced when the doorbell rang.

I hesitated for a long time before I met her, because at home, if I wore a mask, it would seem disrespectful to the Italians. So I have prepared a set of speech mask science.

Even EU governments are Loth to acknowledge the usefulness of face masks, given the "sour grapes" mentality and the "don't be poor, don't be unequal" mentality as countries compete for them in the news.

But all the experts are on the same side as the media, claiming that frequent hand washing can ward off respiratory infections, which is a bit of a puzzle. I offered them another explanation: Because White People's noses are too high and their masks are still drafty, they can't insulate people whose noses are too high.

Yellow people with low noses, like me, are lucky to be able to use my flat face to enjoy the filtered air.

I wore a mask to open the door to her, really face is a naked face, or a plain beauty it.

My upstairs neighbor was drying her sheets on the balcony and accidentally fell into our yard. After learning that I was Chinese, she finally came to pick them up after about two days of psychological struggle.

I handed her the sheet, along with a jar of Shiitake mustard that made me queasy to smell: "It's a Chinese shiitake sauce that goes with the main course and tastes a bit like pickled olives. "

I'm not trying to gross her out. It's a smell the Italians might really like.

"thanks a lot! I've been without food for a week! " She said with a surprised expression

It seems that the recent puffery about China in the Italian media has been very effective. A month ago, when I still dared to go out, every day with the Italians are in the open dialogue, it has been a long time not felt this kind of friendly.

Italy's on lockdown. You have to fill out an application to get out. It was a belated step, but at least Italy came out on top in the European government's race to the bottom.

"I'm not trying to create panic, " as I put it, quoting all the pundits and politicians who must say before speaking. "I'm wearing a mask as a precaution. "

But I know that wearing a mask is of course panic, especially when no one can buy a mask. The biggest worry for everyone is fear mongering, Italy's current heinous crime.

"I'm not trying to create panic, " the expert said. "The new coronavirus is really more serious than the regular flu and should be taken seriously. "

"I'm not trying to create panic, " the politician said. "I just want you to avoid going to mass gatherings. The country won't hold you back for a flu. "

Aside from rounding up the Chinese, the Italians put all their virus-proofing on media alert. Just as the virus is transmitted through the mind, so long as there is a news story that describes the seriousness of the new coronavirus, twenty more people will be infected.

There is definitely psychological evidence that when you take your mind off a wound, the pain your brain perceives is less intense. In the same way, when you don't pay attention to the new coronavirus, you don't get infected.

I was very impressed by the European news in February. There are probably a few institutions similar to the German, Italian and French academies of sciences that say that the new coronavirus is similar to the flu, and that all flu has a certain mortality rate, the common flu can kill 0.3% of those who get it, and the new flu has a case fatality rate of about 0.5% , so don't be too nervous about this particular flu.

I wrote in a note wondering: China's new coronary mortality rate has always been about 2% , is the virus to different races so different lethality?

The expert answers: Because the medical condition of China is not good.

As I type, on the afternoon of March 15th, there were 21,727 confirmed cases in Italy, 1,441 deaths, a case fatality rate of 6.6% .

This alarming figure can probably not be attributed to poor health care in Italy, a country with state of the art technology for treating viral pneumonia; simply because the population is aging incorrectly, the shortage of medical resources must be a major reason.

The Italian government is blunt: The available medical care is so limited that it will have to prioritize treatment for the young, in the hope that the elderly will quarantine themselves.

There have been plenty of eye-opening stories about how things turned out since the evil bat was put on the table.

When I became aware of my own futility, I found that the money I donated could not be donated to Wuhan, and the masks I bought for Italy could not be shipped. The only thing I could do was to put on the masks and create a little panic among the European people. Then those useless emotions, like my home's instant noodles, like the food is depleted.

Every morning the streets are patrolled with cars, loudspeakers blaring advice, and unemotional electronic male voices that brainwash me into half-dream, half-real dilemmas, like the plot of a cybernovel.

I declined my neighbor's offer of baked potatoes. "Are you going to the concert tonight? " She asked

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
One of the programmes of the balcony concert.

This is the Italian people have recently come up with a social way, every night at six o'clock, every family will stand on the balcony with the hi-fi singing. Because Italy's residential buildings in six stories below, and the street is very narrow, balconies are outdoor, very close, you can achieve the effect of empty disco.

"Of course I'll come to your concert. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The artists who performed in the "Balcony Concert" received a large number of messages from China. He thanked them on IG.

She smiled and said yes, leaving the Italian motto: "La Vita Continua come semple.life goes on. ".

It is hard to criticize this kind of happy-in-misery Spirit. Is it fortitude or escape? Life has been so hard.

My classmates have returned home, my eastern European roommates withdrew a month ago, and I am alone in this foreign land, not fighting the virus on the front lines, but worrying about my diploma this year. The world is too confusing for my stupid brain to understand.

I just want every life to be treated well, not abandoned because of age or class.

I don't want to blame these countries for their inexperience, their inexperience, their health care systems, and their finances. I just want to try to save every life. As for all the talk from some political parties that the elderly should die of natural causes a little earlier for the sake of economic development, go away.
